Greek fire chief Christos Smetis confirmed the tragic news that all 115 passengers and six crew members aboard the plane had perished.
Reports indicated previous decompression issues with the aircraft, fueling anger among grieving relatives.
Concerns arose about a potential technical fault that had affected similar Helios planes in the past.
Witnesses described a harrowing scene of blackened bodies and debris scattered in a Greek valley after the crash.
Aviation experts speculated on the possibility of a lack of oxygen causing the tragedy, highlighting the critical importance of cabin pressure in flight safety.
